======================================================================
AXIAL COMPRESSION
======================================================================

3-D axial compression test with linear tetrahedral cells.

-200 <= x <= +200
-200 <= y <= +200


         z=-1.0 m
        ----------
        |        |
x=0.0 m |        | x=0.0 m
y=0.0 m |        | y=0.0 m
        |        |
        ----------
         z=+0.0 m

Dirichlet boundary conditions
  Ux(0,y) = 0.0
  Uy(x,-250) = +1.0 m
  Uy(x,+250) = -1.0 m

Analytical solution
  Ux(x,y) = 0
  Uy(x,y) = 0
  Uz(x,y) = -0.004 * y


======================================================================
SHEAR
======================================================================

3-D shear test with linear tetrahedral cells.

-250 <= x <= +250
-250 <= y <= +250


         ----------
         |        |
y=-1.0 m |        | y=+1.0m
         |        |
         |        |
         ----------


Dirichlet boundary conditions
  Ux(   0,y) =  0.0
  Uy(   0,y) = -1.0 m
  Ux(+250,y) =  0.0
  Uy(+250,y) = +1.0 m

Analytical solution
  Ux(x,y) = 0
  Uy(x,y) = -0.004 * x

